					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469#post-2445647</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469/scp-1555#post-2445647</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 25 Jan 2016 20:31:29 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>sirpudding</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>348648</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>The United States are still on the Imperial system</p> </blockquote> <p>The US was <em>never</em> on the Imperial system, FYI. The US War of Independence ended in 1776, while the Weights and Measures Act wasn't until 1897, over a century later and the US isn't a Commonwealth nation and didn't adopt it. There are significant differences between US Customary and Imperial, most notably between the different tons and gallons and that US Customary doesn't use the stone.</p> <p>Also after 1865, &quot;United States&quot; is a singular, not plural, noun.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469#post-2445641</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469/scp-1555#post-2445641</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 25 Jan 2016 20:16:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Bryx</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1786305</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>They are masquerading as the US government here. The United States is on the US Customary system, so it makes sense that the Foundation would delineate the boundaries of the wildlife sanctuary accordingly. Especially since the size of the area surrounding the skip has absolutely no bearing on the scientific research being done on it, which is where the metrics actually matter.</p> <p>EDIT: Thank you, sirpudding.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
