					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469#post-1422630</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462469/scp-1555#post-1422630</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 20 Apr 2012 20:04:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>genesplicer</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>558043</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I always try to work out the &quot;behind the scenes/backstory&quot; of every SCP I read. I want to know where they came from and what they are for. For this one I envision some alien culture was bent on preserving this species of mouse for some crazy reason, but they wanted to be as unobtrusive as possible. Knowing very little about Human Culture, they figured the Mouse Cannon would blend in nicely. However, the replication program they use has become corrupted over the years, and this accounts for the screwed-up shells that show up from time to time.</p> <p>I also envision the entrance is some sort of intake port. A place for lesser species to provide raw materials that can be converted into mice and cannon shells. The more I want to wonder about something like this, the more I want to upvote. I really have been wondering about this one. Upvoted hard.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
